  Both `review_node` instances (parallel via Send API) return `{"review_file_paths": [output_path]}` at line 337. Without an `operator.add` reducer, LangGraph's merge strategy for parallel branches will use last-write-wins, meaning only one reviewer's path survives. Masked by `collect_reviews` constructing paths from scratch at line 342 — but `architect_node` at line 366 reads `state.get("review_file_paths", [])` for context, which could receive only one path if `collect_reviews` ever fails to override it.

